  SetupScript:
    code: ""
  Description: |-
    Creates a trail mesh for GPU Particles material that uses Trails.
    
    This script is useful for when you need a different amount of segments than the default GPU Particles Trails mesh, which has 100 segments.
    - lowering the segment count helps with performance by reducing the amount of vertices used.
    - increasing segment count fixes visual artifacts such as noticeable segmentation or ends of trails popping in or out.
    - for best results, try to use as few segments as needed to create your effect. Particles with shorter and straighter paths require less segments, while particles with longer or curved paths require more.
